author: Amit Krupal
comment_text: Amit asking Amit. Sirji: I feel proud when our country's company's product is appreciated by our people. In this case yes Tata has literally improved their image with Tiago,Tigor & Hexa. Never trusted safety & build quality of Maruti cars. Now what factors should be consider while buying a car for 1st time. I own Bajaj Avenger 150 street, completed 10,200 kms. Its an awesome practical ride. Gives consistent 45 kpl only when you use Castrol/Motul Engine oil in Avenger 150. Only problem so far is with Bajaj Service centers, arrogant & ignorant service center. Now I am only considering Tata cars, even though after having bad experience with Bajaj Service center. My friends who own Maruti's Eeco & Hyundai's Xcent had similar bad experience. Eeco's spare tyre was stolen from service center whereas Xcent's Cracked bumper was welded but they said & charged the owner with replacement bumper. So nowadays it better to not trust whatever the service center claims, but to verify their services. Now coming back to question I am in need of car for my family of 4. Considering Tiago/Tigor/Nexon(only if its reasonable). What features should be considering for 1st time car owner?I obviously love Nexon more than Tiago/Tigor, but is the price difference justifiable. Also since I am buying 1st car of my life, my enthusiasm may make me take my car to long rides. Considering the needs are simple, Safe, reliable, practical & stylish car. I am a freelance photographer will be expanding my business, so in future I may need my car to accommodate 4 people with lot of camera gear to in terms of boot space Tigor is attracting me most. But when it comes to roads condition especially in Mumbai, Nexon's ride is attracting me more. No which one to decide.

author: Amit Krupal
comment_text: Amit asking Amit. Sirji: I feel proud when our country's company's product is appreciated by our people. In this case yes Tata has literally improved their image with Tiago,Tigor & Hexa. Never trusted safety & build quality of Maruti cars. Now what factors should be consider while buying a car for 1st time. I own Bajaj Avenger 150 street, completed 10,200 kms. Its an awesome practical ride. Gives consistent 45 kpl only when you use Castrol/Motul Engine oil in Avenger 150. Only problem so far is with Bajaj Service centers, arrogant & ignorant service center. Now I am only considering Tata cars, even though after having bad experience with Bajaj Service center. My friends who own Maruti's Eeco & Hyundai's Xcent had similar bad experience. Eeco's spare tyre was stolen from service center whereas Xcent's Cracked bumper was welded but they said & charged the owner with replacement bumper. So nowadays it better to not trust whatever the service center claims, but to verify their services. Now coming back to question I am in need of car for my family of 4. Considering Tiago/Tigor/Nexon(only if its reasonable). What features should be considering for 1st time car owner?I obviously love Nexon more than Tiago/Tigor, but is the price difference justifiable. Also since I am buying 1st car of my life, my enthusiasm may make me take my car to long rides. Considering the needs are simple, Safe, reliable, practical & stylish car. I am a freelance photographer will be expanding my business, so in future I may need my car to accommodate 4 people with lot of camera gear to in terms of boot space Tigor is attracting me most. But when it comes to roads condition especially in Mumbai, Nexon's ride is attracting me more. No which one to decide.

author: Amit Krupal
comment_text: Amit asking Amit. Sirji: I feel proud when our country's company's product is appreciated by our people. In this case yes Tata has literally improved their image with Tiago,Tigor & Hexa. Never trusted safety & build quality of Maruti cars. Now what factors should be consider while buying a car for 1st time. I own Bajaj Avenger 150 street, completed 10,200 kms. Its an awesome practical ride. Gives consistent 45 kpl only when you use Castrol/Motul Engine oil in Avenger 150. Only problem so far is with Bajaj Service centers, arrogant & ignorant service center. Now I am only considering Tata cars, even though after having bad experience with Bajaj Service center. My friends who own Maruti's Eeco & Hyundai's Xcent had similar bad experience. Eeco's spare tyre was stolen from service center whereas Xcent's Cracked bumper was welded but they said & charged the owner with replacement bumper. So nowadays it better to not trust whatever the service center claims, but to verify their services. Now coming back to question I am in need of car for my family of 4. Considering Tiago/Tigor/Nexon(only if its reasonable). What features should be considering for 1st time car owner?I obviously love Nexon more than Tiago/Tigor, but is the price difference justifiable. Also since I am buying 1st car of my life, my enthusiasm may make me take my car to long rides. Considering the needs are simple, Safe, reliable, practical & stylish car. I am a freelance photographer will be expanding my business, so in future I may need my car to accommodate 4 people with lot of camera gear to in terms of boot space Tigor is attracting me most. But when it comes to roads condition especially in Mumbai, Nexon's ride is attracting me more. No which one to decide.

author: Amit Krupal
comment_text: Amit asking Amit. Sirji: I feel proud when our country's company's product is appreciated by our people. In this case yes Tata has literally improved their image with Tiago,Tigor & Hexa. Never trusted safety & build quality of Maruti cars. Now what factors should be consider while buying a car for 1st time. I own Bajaj Avenger 150 street, completed 10,200 kms. Its an awesome practical ride. Gives consistent 45 kpl only when you use Castrol/Motul Engine oil in Avenger 150. Only problem so far is with Bajaj Service centers, arrogant & ignorant service center. Now I am only considering Tata cars, even though after having bad experience with Bajaj Service center. My friends who own Maruti's Eeco & Hyundai's Xcent had similar bad experience. Eeco's spare tyre was stolen from service center whereas Xcent's Cracked bumper was welded but they said & charged the owner with replacement bumper. So nowadays it better to not trust whatever the service center claims, but to verify their services. Now coming back to question I am in need of car for my family of 4. Considering Tiago/Tigor/Nexon(only if its reasonable). What features should be considering for 1st time car owner?I obviously love Nexon more than Tiago/Tigor, but is the price difference justifiable. Also since I am buying 1st car of my life, my enthusiasm may make me take my car to long rides. Considering the needs are simple, Safe, reliable, practical & stylish car. I am a freelance photographer will be expanding my business, so in future I may need my car to accommodate 4 people with lot of camera gear to in terms of boot space Tigor is attracting me most. But when it comes to roads condition especially in Mumbai, Nexon's ride is attracting me more. No which one to decide.

author: Amit Krupal
comment_text: Amit asking Amit. Sirji: I feel proud when our country's company's product is appreciated by our people. In this case yes Tata has literally improved their image with Tiago,Tigor & Hexa. Never trusted safety & build quality of Maruti cars. Now what factors should be consider while buying a car for 1st time. I own Bajaj Avenger 150 street, completed 10,200 kms. Its an awesome practical ride. Gives consistent 45 kpl only when you use Castrol/Motul Engine oil in Avenger 150. Only problem so far is with Bajaj Service centers, arrogant & ignorant service center. Now I am only considering Tata cars, even though after having bad experience with Bajaj Service center. My friends who own Maruti's Eeco & Hyundai's Xcent had similar bad experience. Eeco's spare tyre was stolen from service center whereas Xcent's Cracked bumper was welded but they said & charged the owner with replacement bumper. So nowadays it better to not trust whatever the service center claims, but to verify their services. Now coming back to question I am in need of car for my family of 4. Considering Tiago/Tigor/Nexon(only if its reasonable). What features should be considering for 1st time car owner?I obviously love Nexon more than Tiago/Tigor, but is the price difference justifiable. Also since I am buying 1st car of my life, my enthusiasm may make me take my car to long rides. Considering the needs are simple, Safe, reliable, practical & stylish car. I am a freelance photographer will be expanding my business, so in future I may need my car to accommodate 4 people with lot of camera gear to in terms of boot space Tigor is attracting me most. But when it comes to roads condition especially in Mumbai, Nexon's ride is attracting me more. No which one to decide.

author: Amit Krupal
comment_text: Amit asking Amit. Sirji: I feel proud when our country's company's product is appreciated by our people. In this case yes Tata has literally improved their image with Tiago,Tigor & Hexa. Never trusted safety & build quality of Maruti cars. Now what factors should be consider while buying a car for 1st time. I own Bajaj Avenger 150 street, completed 10,200 kms. Its an awesome practical ride. Gives consistent 45 kpl only when you use Castrol/Motul Engine oil in Avenger 150. Only problem so far is with Bajaj Service centers, arrogant & ignorant service center. Now I am only considering Tata cars, even though after having bad experience with Bajaj Service center. My friends who own Maruti's Eeco & Hyundai's Xcent had similar bad experience. Eeco's spare tyre was stolen from service center whereas Xcent's Cracked bumper was welded but they said & charged the owner with replacement bumper. So nowadays it better to not trust whatever the service center claims, but to verify their services. Now coming back to question I am in need of car for my family of 4. Considering Tiago/Tigor/Nexon(only if its reasonable). What features should be considering for 1st time car owner?I obviously love Nexon more than Tiago/Tigor, but is the price difference justifiable. Also since I am buying 1st car of my life, my enthusiasm may make me take my car to long rides. Considering the needs are simple, Safe, reliable, practical & stylish car. I am a freelance photographer will be expanding my business, so in future I may need my car to accommodate 4 people with lot of camera gear to in terms of boot space Tigor is attracting me most. But when it comes to roads condition especially in Mumbai, Nexon's ride is attracting me more. No which one to decide.
